    <!-- The contents of <statement></statement> should specify
         the task you wish them to complete. -->
    <statement>
        <p>
Explain how to find the following for the function <m>f(x)=x^{3} - 9 \, x^{2} + 15 \, x - 3</m>.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
The open intervals where <m>f(x)</m> is increasing or decreasing.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
The relative extrema of <m>f(x)</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>

    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
The function increases on <m>(-\infty,1)</m>,
decreases on <m>(1,5)</m>, and increases on
<m>(5,\infty)</m>.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
The point <m>(x,y)=(1,4)</m> is a relative maximum,
and the point <m>(x,y)=(5,-28)</m> is a relative minimum.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
